Pokmon Dataset Analysis

Overview

This document explores various attributes of Pokmon using data from the provided dataset. Well create visualizations, analyze characteristics, and uncover interesting insights.

Dataset Description

  • Name: The English name of the Pokmon
  • Japanese Name: The Original Japanese name of the Pokmon
  • Pokedex Number: The entry number of the Pokmon in the National Pokedex
  • Percentage Male: The percentage of the male species (blank if genderless)
  • Type 1: The Primary Type of the Pokmon
  • Type 2: The Secondary Type of the Pokmon
  • Classification: The Pokmons classification as described by the Sun and Moon Pokedex
  • Height (m): Height of the Pokmon in meters
  • Weight (kg): The Weight of the Pokmon in kilograms
  • Capture Rate: Capture Rate of the Pokmon
  • Base Egg Steps: The number of steps required to hatch an egg of the Pokmon
  • Abilities: A stringified list of abilities that the Pokmon is capable of having
  • Experience Growth: The Experience Growth of the Pokmon
  • Base Happiness: Base Happiness of the Pokmon
  • Against_?: Eighteen features that denote the amount of damage taken against an attack of a particular type
  • HP: The Base HP of the Pokmon
  • Attack: The Base Attack of the Pokmon
  • Defense: The Base Defense of the Pokmon
  • Special Attack: The Base Special Attack of the Pokmon
  • Special Defense: The Base Special Defense of the Pokmon
  • Speed: The Base Speed of the Pokmon
  • Generation: The numbered generation in which the Pokmon was first introduced
  • Is Legendary: Denotes if the Pokmon is legendary

  name = c("Pikachu", "Charizard", "Bulbasaur", "Squirtle", "Jigglypuff"),
  height_m = c(0.4, 1.7, 0.7, 0.5, 0.5),
  weight_kg = c(6, 90.5, 6.9, 9, 5.5)
)

Scatter plot: Height vs.Weight

ggplot(merged_pokemon_data_frame, aes(x = height_m, y = weight_kg)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = as.factor(height_m > median(height_m))), size = 3) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("blue", "red"), 
                     name = "Height relative to median", 
                     labels = c("Below or equal to median", "Above median")) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "black", linetype = "dashed") +
  labs(title = "Pokmon Height vs. Weight",
       subtitle = "Each point represents a Pokmon",
       caption = "Data source: Pokmon database",
       x = "Height (meters)",
       y = "Weight (kilograms)") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
        plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "italic"),
        plot.caption = element_text(hjust = 1, face = "italic"))
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

Pie Chart: Gender Distribution

# Calculate the percentage of females for each type
merged_pokemon_data$percentage_female <- 100 - merged_pokemon_data$percentage_male

# Reshape the data
reshaped_data <- merged_pokemon_data %>%
  gather(key = "gender", value = "percentage", percentage_male, percentage_female)

# Plot
ggplot(reshaped_data, aes(x = type1, y = percentage, fill = gender)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "stack") +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2", name = "Gender") +
  labs(title = "Gender Distribution of Pokmon Types",
       subtitle = "Each bar represents a Pokmon type",
       caption = "Data source: Pokmon database",
       x = "Type",
       y = "Percentage") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
        plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "italic"),
        plot.caption = element_text(hjust = 1, face = "italic"),
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))  # Rotate x-axis labels

Density Plot: Pokmon Speed Distribution
